&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 7 head and neck cancer nurse specialist team leader &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Full time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;External advert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you an experienced clinical nurse specialist (CNS) looking to take on the challenge of a team leader position or have you extensive experience in caring for patients with head and neck cancers at band 6 level or above? If so we would love to hear from you as we are looking to recruit to the Band 7 CNS team leader position in the head and neck cancer team at Leeds Teaching Hospital Trust. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a regional cancer service supporting patients diagnosed with head and neck cancers undergoing treatments including surgery, chemotherapy and radiotherapy. The CNS team form part of a close working multi-disciplinary team providing expert cancer advice with dedicated enteral feeding support and airway management. As well as carrying your own patient case load, the CNS team leader will be expected to support the established team of band 6 CNS’s &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;and help lead on service improvements, working closely with the community teams, referring hospitals and the Leeds Cancer Team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please read the attached job description closely to ensure you have met all of the criteria before applying. Whilst we are advertising for a full time position, part time at 30hrs per week would also be considered. We look forward to hearing from you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Informal enquires can be made by contacting Sally Wild, Matron on 0113 2066400 or by email &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;sallywild@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
